		</docu>
	~]]></Comment><Type Namespace="TcoCore">eMessageCategory</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize></Parameter><Local><Name>_tmpMessage</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">TcoMessage</Type><BitSize>1600</BitSize></Local></Method><Properties><Property><Name>PouType</Name><Value>FunctionBlock</Value></Property></Properties></DataType><DataType><Name Namespace="TcoCore">TcoContext</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Root construction container, provides context information for <c>TcoObjects</c> declared within its scope.
			This function block is ```abstract``` and cannot be instantiated. 
			Use <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoContext.Run()"/> to run this context, ```Run``` method must be called only once per PLC Task cycle.
			Several 'TcoContext' instances can be declared and called inside one TwinCAT PlcTask, but only once per PLC cycle. 
			The instance should not be accessed from several Twincat PlcTasks.
			Default implemenation of the 'TcoContext' allows its child members access properties <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoContext.StartCycleCount()"/> 
			and <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoContext.EndCycleCount()"/>, messenger settings, rtc and other information related to the context of the running logic.			 			 			
			<note type="tip">
				 A <c>TcoContext</c> can contain objects, components and PLC logic of one independent station of the machine, 
				 while the another one can cover the same for another station.			
			</note>
			<remarks>			
				<note type="tip">
					TwinCAT PlcTask and <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoTask()"/> refer to two different concepts. 
				</note>
			</remarks>
		</summary>	
		<example>
			Declaration part of the 'TcoContext' example. 
		</example>
		<example>
				[!code-pas[Main](~/../TcOpen/src/TcoApplicationExamples/XaeAppExamples/PlcAppExamples/POUs/Context/VitoCorleone_Context.TcPOU?name=ContextExampleDeclarations)]
		</example>
		<example>
			Implementation part of the 'TcoContext' example.
		</example>
		<example>
				[!code-pas[Main](~/../TcOpen/src/TcoApplicationExamples/XaeAppExamples/PlcAppExamples/POUs/Context/VitoCorleone_Context.TcPOU?name=ContextExampleCode)]
		</example>
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><BitSize>1623744</BitSize><Implements Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoContext</Implements><SubItem><Name>_Identity</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><BitOffs>64</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_startCycleCount</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><BitOffs>128</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_endCycleCount</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize><BitOffs>192</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_messagingLevel</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">eMessageCategory</Type><BitSize>16</BitSize><BitOffs>256</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_rtc</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">TcoRtc</Type><BitSize>6784</BitSize><BitOffs>288</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_settings</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">TcoContextEnvironment</Type><BitSize>2304</BitSize><BitOffs>7072</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_logger</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">TcoLogger</Type><BitSize>1608128</BitSize><BitOffs>9408</BitOffs></SubItem><SubItem><Name>_timeSychnMessenger</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">TcoMessenger</Type><BitSize>6208</BitSize><BitOffs>1617536</BitOffs></SubItem><Method><Name>__getContext</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
