	<docu>
		<summary>
			Called upon exit from the context. When overridden in derived class allows to execute an arbitrary logic after closing the context cycle.	
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></Method><Method><Name>Run</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			<para>
				This method executes of this context. It provided correct order of execution order of inner methods. Any logic of this context must be called within <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoContext.Main()"/>
				method. This method is final, so it cannot be overriden. The <c>InstanceName.Run()</c> needs to be called cyclically.
			</para>
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment></Method><Method><Name>__getEnvironment</Name><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoContextEnvironment</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Local><Name>Environment</Name><Type Namespace="TcoCore">ITcoContextEnvironment</Type><BitSize>32</BitSize></Local><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>__getEndCycleCount</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
		    Gets the value of the counter incrememented by '1' at the end of each execution of this <see cref="PlcDocu.TcoCore.TcoContext()"/>.			
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType>ULINT</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>64</ReturnBitSize><Local><Name>EndCycleCount</Name><Type>ULINT</Type><BitSize>64</BitSize></Local><Properties><Property><Name>property</Name></Property></Properties></Method><Method><Name>RtcSynchronize</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
	<docu>
		<summary>
			Syncronizes the Real Time Clock (RTC) from given source.
			<remarks>			
				<note type="important">
					There is single RTC source for entire application. All context share the same RTC source.
				</note>
			</remarks>
		</summary>			
	</docu>	
~]]></Comment><ReturnType Namespace="TcoCore" ReferenceTo="true">TcoContext</ReturnType><ReturnBitSize>32</ReturnBitSize><Parameter><Name>inDoSynch</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
		<docu>
			<summary>
				When called with true the synchronization mechanism executes.		
			</summary>			
		</docu>	
	~]]></Comment><Type>BOOL</Type><BitSize>8</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>inSyncAmsId</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
		<docu>
			<summary>
				```AMS ID``` of the system against which RTC of this application will synchronize.			
			</summary>			
		</docu>	
	~]]></Comment><Type>STRING(80)</Type><BitSize>648</BitSize></Parameter><Parameter><Name>inSyncPeriod</Name><Comment><![CDATA[~
